  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;for the Global Green Finance Leadership Program&quot;</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;China, currently the largest carbon emitter, is committed to reducing emissions to meet the Paris Agreement. To transition to a low-carbon economy, market interventions are needed. Green finance can help steer private capital into climate-friendly industries and projects. The Research Center for Green Finance Development at Tsinghua University expects to accomplish two goals with this Program: (a) to accelerate the domestic development of green finance and (b) to build the capacity for green finance with international partners.&quot;</narrative>
  </description>
